                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Tämälläs-sign, in the shape of two perpendicular lines (┴), indicating the place where the omission, written in the upper margin, belongs: fol. 13ra.&#xD;
- Omitted word inserted interlineally: fol. 13ra.&#xD;
- Erasures: e.g., fols. 51vb, 60ara, 67ra, 74ra, 90vb, 107vb.&#xD;
- Corrections written over erasures in the main hand: e.g., fols. 48ra, 92va, 110ra, 132vb.&#xD;
- Immediate corrections indicated by dashes above and below the letters: fol. 79rb.&#xD;
- Lacunae (spaces for rubrication left unfilled): fol. 156ra.&#xD;
- Cues for the rubricator written in the margin: fol. 108ra.&#xD;
- Scribbles in blue pen or in pencil: e.g., fols. 49r, 60v, 68v, 72v.&#xD;
- Several names are written interlineally in a secondary hand in strong fuchsia ink: Wäldä Maryam (e.g., fols. 17va, 41vb, 88vb, 97va, 111va, 129rb, 154rb), ʾAmätä Maryam (e.g., fols. 15va, 89rb, 95ra, 116rb, 138vb, 160va), Gäbrä Yoḥannǝs (e.g., fols. 44ra, 101rb, 142vb, 162va), Täklä ʾƎgziʾ (e.g., fols. 50ra, 103rb, 124ra, 149ra), Wälättä Täklä Haymanot (e.g., fols. 79ra, 81ra), Wälättä Maryam (fols. 81rb, 81va).</item>
